This paper deals with image synthesis, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning for MR image synthesis, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates different normalization algorithms, which involves statistical methods and optimization, making it relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
